WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

00:00:18.940 --> 00:00:23.880
笙ｪOnly after bloom comes fruit笙ｪ

00:00:25.290 --> 00:00:29.260
笙ｪWho says glory must fade to the past笙ｪ

00:00:31.920 --> 00:00:37.010
笙ｪOnly through thunder
do you reach the clouds笙ｪ

00:00:38.210 --> 00:00:43.120
笙ｪWho made you the crown of every peak笙ｪ

00:00:44.650 --> 00:00:47.930
笙ｪI stand at the center of the stage笙ｪ

00:00:47.930 --> 00:00:51.000
笙ｪMy shadow is pinned against the wall笙ｪ

00:00:51.710 --> 00:00:56.660
笙ｪFacing the light earns every medal笙ｪ

00:00:57.700 --> 00:01:00.880
笙ｪLittle birds,
save your needless pecking笙ｪ

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:04.160
笙ｪThe open sky rises high笙ｪ

00:01:04.700 --> 00:01:09.830
笙ｪWhen night falls,
the moon begins to shine笙ｪ

00:01:10.600 --> 00:01:13.860
笙ｪI stand in the heart of these lands笙ｪ

00:01:13.860 --> 00:01:17.220
笙ｪMy shadow bears no crown or robe笙ｪ

00:01:17.630 --> 00:01:23.300
笙ｪThen I know truth needs no disguise笙ｪ

00:01:23.710 --> 00:01:26.960
笙ｪThe green hills see me as I am笙ｪ

00:01:26.960 --> 00:01:30.290
笙ｪLike dew, lightning,
and moon on the river笙ｪ

00:01:30.690 --> 00:01:34.730
笙ｪShowing me exactly who I am笙ｪ

00:01:34.730 --> 00:01:35.980
=The Lead=

00:01:36.060 --> 00:01:37.940
=Episode 10=

00:02:09.520 --> 00:02:10.360
Laidi.

00:02:11.010 --> 00:02:12.310
Come on, come here.

00:02:18.070 --> 00:02:19.200
See? That's political awareness.

00:02:20.200 --> 00:02:21.710
Why are you writing this?

00:02:21.710 --> 00:02:22.550
Why?

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:25.200
Chu Jiahe and Feng Xiaoxiao
got everyone to write letters

00:02:25.520 --> 00:02:26.640
and donate money.

00:02:27.070 --> 00:02:29.110
Director Huang praised them.

00:02:29.240 --> 00:02:30.430
They got all that honor.

00:02:30.960 --> 00:02:31.840
Inside that honor of theirs,

00:02:31.840 --> 00:02:33.470
my fifteen cents was in there too.

00:02:33.470 --> 00:02:35.110
But I got no praise at all.

00:02:35.110 --> 00:02:35.950
So unfair.

00:02:36.520 --> 00:02:38.470
No, twenty cents.

00:02:38.470 --> 00:02:39.710
I forgot your five cents.

00:02:39.710 --> 00:02:41.230
I'll pay you back.

00:02:41.230 --> 00:02:42.070
Okay.

00:02:43.760 --> 00:02:44.600
Look at this.

00:02:45.590 --> 00:02:47.430
If this gets posted outside

00:02:47.430 --> 00:02:49.040
and then gets seen by Director Huang,

00:02:50.000 --> 00:02:51.310
will he praise us?

00:02:51.710 --> 00:02:54.350
Aren't you missing punctuation?

00:02:54.350 --> 00:02:55.190
Right.

00:02:55.680 --> 00:02:56.560
That's easy.

00:03:01.310 --> 00:03:05.200
Not a period. An exclamation mark.

00:03:05.680 --> 00:03:06.840
Then that's easier.

00:03:14.840 --> 00:03:15.680
Who's there?

00:03:18.070 --> 00:03:20.350
Keep staring, and I'll smack you both.

00:03:21.350 --> 00:03:22.190
What's wrong with him?

00:03:22.350 --> 00:03:23.790
He got stung by a scorpion.

00:03:26.510 --> 00:03:27.350
How do you know?

00:03:30.640 --> 00:03:31.510
Section Chief's wife.

00:03:32.200 --> 00:03:33.230
Come help me lift this.

00:03:33.230 --> 00:03:39.940
(People's Communes are good?)

00:03:39.950 --> 00:03:42.350
Why yell so early? You scared me.

00:03:42.350 --> 00:03:44.120
What kind of flip was that?

00:03:44.120 --> 00:03:45.120
How have you been training?

00:03:46.080 --> 00:03:47.430
Those steamed stuffed buns were wasted.

00:03:47.800 --> 00:03:48.960
Stop flipping around.

00:03:48.960 --> 00:03:49.800
We're cooking.

00:03:49.820 --> 00:03:51.400
You'll kick dirt everywhere.

00:03:51.870 --> 00:03:55.080
He's just a troublemaker, no sense at all.

00:03:58.590 --> 00:03:59.520
Mr. He!

00:03:59.750 --> 00:04:00.590
What?

00:04:01.030 --> 00:04:02.080
Good morning.

00:04:03.120 --> 00:04:05.080
This little brat even learned manners.

00:04:06.560 --> 00:04:07.750
Keep practicing routines!

00:04:08.190 --> 00:04:10.400
The slow bird can't rest.

00:04:11.590 --> 00:04:13.360
Dachui, we've got a treat for lunch.

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:14.840
What's with everyone?

00:04:15.800 --> 00:04:16.640
Went blind?

00:04:26.630 --> 00:04:27.470
Hua Caixiang.

00:04:32.400 --> 00:04:33.590
Last night,

00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:35.560
I made a long-distance call

00:04:37.190 --> 00:04:38.560
to Comrade Zhang Guangrong

00:04:40.060 --> 00:04:40.910
and told him

00:04:40.910 --> 00:04:42.680
everything about your situation.

00:04:44.080 --> 00:04:44.920
What situation?

00:04:45.400 --> 00:04:46.710
Your pregnancy, and your

00:04:46.960 --> 00:04:48.080
request for an abortion.

00:04:50.840 --> 00:04:51.680
What did he say?

00:04:51.870 --> 00:04:53.910
He strongly opposed the abortion.

00:04:54.630 --> 00:04:55.560
He also said

00:04:55.560 --> 00:04:56.590
he's withdrawing

00:04:56.590 --> 00:04:58.080
his agreement to divorce you.

00:05:08.190 --> 00:05:09.030
I'm asking for leave.

00:05:10.190 --> 00:05:11.640
- What leave?
- Family visit leave.

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:13.800
I leave today. To visit Zhang Guangrong.

00:05:25.580 --> 00:05:33.900
(People's Communes are good?)

00:05:33.910 --> 00:05:36.430
All this time. Are they blind?

00:05:40.360 --> 00:05:41.430
I know why now.

00:05:43.520 --> 00:05:44.360
Why?

00:05:47.080 --> 00:05:48.030
Hello, Director Huang.

00:05:48.630 --> 00:05:49.680
Step away from the wall.

00:06:00.540 --> 00:06:02.420
(People's Communes are good?)

00:06:04.480 --> 00:06:05.320
Who wrote this?

00:06:05.510 --> 00:06:06.350
We did.

00:06:06.470 --> 00:06:07.310
Who told you to write it?

00:06:07.430 --> 00:06:09.560
No one. We wrote it ourselves.

00:06:10.310 --> 00:06:11.360
Yourselves?

00:06:11.360 --> 00:06:12.950
Little counterrevolutionary!

00:06:12.950 --> 00:06:14.270
Little counterrevolutionary! That's you!

00:06:14.270 --> 00:06:15.950
- Ow, ow! It hurts!
- Counterrevolutionary! No good!

00:06:15.950 --> 00:06:17.310
The Central People's Broadcasting Station,

00:06:17.430 --> 00:06:20.240
at 4 P.M., will have

00:06:20.390 --> 00:06:22.240
an important broadcast.

00:06:22.680 --> 00:06:24.190
Please stay tuned.

00:06:24.510 --> 00:06:26.510
The Central People's Broadcasting Station,

00:06:26.870 --> 00:06:29.390
at 4 P.M., will have...

00:06:29.430 --> 00:06:36.480
笙ｪWe all live beneath the sky笙ｪ

00:06:36.950 --> 00:06:44.120
笙ｪYet each fate takes its own road笙ｪ

00:06:44.720 --> 00:06:48.070
笙ｪI am just an ordinary big brick笙ｪ

00:06:48.480 --> 00:06:52.040
笙ｪMoved wherever I am needed笙ｪ

00:06:52.040 --> 00:06:56.390
笙ｪBuilt in city walls, I feel no conceit笙ｪ

00:06:56.390 --> 00:06:58.360
笙ｪOr laid in a latrine笙ｪ

00:07:09.800 --> 00:07:10.640
Laidi.

00:07:14.120 --> 00:07:14.960
What are you doing?

00:07:15.360 --> 00:07:16.630
Looking for Heiwa.

00:07:17.800 --> 00:07:18.950
I pulled some strings.

00:07:19.270 --> 00:07:20.680
Your uncle gets out tomorrow.

00:07:24.190 --> 00:07:25.560
Give this letter to him.

00:07:26.480 --> 00:07:27.360
Where are you going?

00:07:28.680 --> 00:07:30.830
To the provincial capital. Big business.

00:07:31.430 --> 00:07:33.000
Your uncle is a spineless coward.

00:07:34.360 --> 00:07:35.920
I'm leaving. Hurry home.

00:07:35.920 --> 00:07:36.920
Don't wander around outside.

00:07:57.060 --> 00:08:03.300
(Everyone participates in
protecting our home)

00:08:05.680 --> 00:08:07.310
Heiwa, what are you doing here?

00:08:08.190 --> 00:08:09.630
It's raining! Go.

00:08:10.070 --> 00:08:10.910
Leave me alone.

00:08:11.360 --> 00:08:12.560
You can't stand here soaking wet.

00:08:12.560 --> 00:08:13.800
Come with me!

00:08:14.480 --> 00:08:16.040
Go on. Leave me alone!

00:08:17.390 --> 00:08:19.070
Hurry. Go.

00:08:27.510 --> 00:08:28.680
Why did he hit you

00:08:29.240 --> 00:08:30.630
and call you counterrevolutionary?

00:08:35.360 --> 00:08:36.270
How would I know?

00:08:53.120 --> 00:08:53.960
Look!

00:08:54.310 --> 00:08:55.180
At what?

00:08:55.240 --> 00:08:56.080
Look over there.

00:08:56.510 --> 00:08:58.870
A line and a dot make an exclamation mark.

00:08:59.430 --> 00:09:00.680
We wrote it wrong.

00:09:00.680 --> 00:09:01.980
(People's Communes are good!)

00:09:03.240 --> 00:09:05.000
Then what did we write?

00:09:06.430 --> 00:09:08.120
Oh no. A question mark?

00:09:10.830 --> 00:09:12.430
Did we make a huge mistake?

00:09:12.430 --> 00:09:13.270
I don't know.

00:09:18.270 --> 00:09:19.310
It's all your fault!

00:09:20.310 --> 00:09:21.430
What did I do?

00:09:21.430 --> 00:09:23.040
You made me add punctuation.

00:09:23.040 --> 00:09:24.430
But everyone else did it.

00:09:24.430 --> 00:09:26.270
Look there. They wrote it too.

00:09:26.630 --> 00:09:27.830
You want to get me in trouble.

00:09:45.600 --> 00:09:46.680
What's with the sky?

00:09:53.820 --> 00:09:55.660
(People's Communes are good!)

00:09:55.680 --> 00:09:57.480
That last chime just now

00:09:57.750 --> 00:10:00.950
marked 16:00 Beijing time.

00:10:01.920 --> 00:10:03.950
The Central Committee

00:10:04.310 --> 00:10:06.240
of the Communist Party of China,

00:10:06.830 --> 00:10:11.910
the Standing Committee of
the National People's Congress,

00:10:13.000 --> 00:10:14.550
the State Council,

00:10:16.750 --> 00:10:19.390
and the Central Military Commission,

00:10:20.550 --> 00:10:27.000
with deepest grief, announce
to the Party, the Army,

00:10:27.000 --> 00:10:30.550
and the people of all ethnic
groups across the country:

00:10:32.630 --> 00:10:33.720
the beloved great leader

00:10:34.270 --> 00:10:35.750
and great mentor

00:10:36.600 --> 00:10:39.150
of our Party, our Army,

00:10:39.910 --> 00:10:43.150
and the people of all ethnic groups

00:10:44.150 --> 00:10:46.510
in our country,

00:10:47.480 --> 00:10:49.440
Comrade Mao Zedong,

00:10:50.720 --> 00:10:52.630
after failing to respond

00:10:53.440 --> 00:10:55.600
to medical treatment

00:10:55.600 --> 00:11:00.630
due to illness, passed away in Beijing

00:11:01.360 --> 00:11:03.480
at 12:10 A.M.

00:11:03.840 --> 00:11:07.240
on September 9, 1976.

00:11:43.600 --> 00:11:45.440
Did I really make a huge mistake?

00:11:46.390 --> 00:11:48.080
Maybe we should go back.

00:11:48.550 --> 00:11:49.600
If I go back now,

00:11:50.030 --> 00:11:51.790
Huang Zhengjing will beat me up.

00:11:59.510 --> 00:12:00.480
Where are you going?

00:12:02.240 --> 00:12:03.080
Heiwa.

00:12:27.320 --> 00:12:28.440
Which way are we going?

00:12:34.440 --> 00:12:35.910
It's getting dark.

00:12:36.270 --> 00:12:37.600
Maybe we should head back.

00:12:38.870 --> 00:12:39.910
If I go back,

00:12:41.600 --> 00:12:43.360
Huang Zhengjing will beat me up.

00:13:36.960 --> 00:13:37.840
The earth didn't shake,

00:13:39.670 --> 00:13:40.750
but the sky collapsed.

00:13:54.320 --> 00:13:55.840
Now you've left us.

00:13:55.840 --> 00:13:58.140
(In memory)

00:13:58.200 --> 00:13:59.630
What are we supposed to do?

00:14:18.240 --> 00:14:20.000
They must be searching everywhere for us.

00:14:23.600 --> 00:14:24.840
If they catch me,

00:14:25.270 --> 00:14:26.440
will they lock me up?

00:14:28.080 --> 00:14:30.440
The inventor of the question
mark should be locked up.

00:14:32.960 --> 00:14:35.200
Same for whoever invented words.

00:14:36.240 --> 00:14:38.270
And whoever invented opera too.

00:14:39.360 --> 00:14:40.390
If I'd been herding sheep,

00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:42.120
none of this would've happened.

00:15:51.390 --> 00:15:52.230
Heiwa.

00:15:52.720 --> 00:15:53.560
Heiwa.

00:15:57.750 --> 00:15:58.720
Where are we?

00:15:59.600 --> 00:16:00.630
The threshing ground.

00:16:01.480 --> 00:16:03.030
What were you mumbling?

00:16:04.120 --> 00:16:05.390
I'm starving.

00:16:06.030 --> 00:16:07.000
Me too.

00:16:14.910 --> 00:16:17.480
The potato is so tiny. It hasn't grown up.

00:16:17.480 --> 00:16:18.670
Forget it. If we wait for it to grow,

00:16:18.670 --> 00:16:19.870
we won't get to grow up.

00:16:20.480 --> 00:16:21.320
Just dig.

00:16:21.670 --> 00:16:22.840
What are you doing?

00:16:23.720 --> 00:16:25.270
The Little Red Guards saw us. Run!

00:16:25.270 --> 00:16:26.600
Stop!

00:16:26.600 --> 00:16:27.440
Don't run!

00:16:27.440 --> 00:16:29.440
The class enemy stole potatoes!

00:16:30.960 --> 00:16:33.150
Give them back, now!

00:16:33.150 --> 00:16:35.030
The class enemy stole potatoes!

00:16:35.630 --> 00:16:36.470
Stop!

00:16:36.600 --> 00:16:37.910
Give back the potatoes!

00:16:38.120 --> 00:16:40.510
Catch the class enemy!

00:16:40.510 --> 00:16:41.360
Stop!

00:16:42.600 --> 00:16:43.670
Don't run!

00:16:44.320 --> 00:16:46.360
The class enemy stole potatoes!

00:16:46.360 --> 00:16:48.550
- Don't run!
- Stop!

00:16:48.840 --> 00:16:50.670
Stop if you've got the nerve!

00:16:50.670 --> 00:16:52.510
You two, hurry up!

00:17:02.510 --> 00:17:03.750
What are you doing?

00:17:03.750 --> 00:17:05.480
You can't eat raw potatoes.

00:17:05.480 --> 00:17:06.340
Why not?

00:17:06.360 --> 00:17:07.440
They'll poison you.

00:17:14.440 --> 00:17:16.000
So I was chased as a class enemy

00:17:16.000 --> 00:17:17.270
for nothing all that time.

00:17:20.270 --> 00:17:21.630
I had a dream last night.

00:17:23.440 --> 00:17:24.360
One moment, I was

00:17:25.200 --> 00:17:26.480
Dong Cunrui blowing up a bunker.

00:17:27.550 --> 00:17:29.200
Then I was Huang Jiguang at the gun port.

00:17:29.550 --> 00:17:31.080
Director Huang said I'm

00:17:31.080 --> 00:17:32.200
not a counterrevolutionary.

00:17:33.120 --> 00:17:34.200
Instead, I'm

00:17:35.000 --> 00:17:35.870
a combat hero.

00:17:38.870 --> 00:17:40.120
If only the dream were real.

00:17:40.840 --> 00:17:41.870
Then we'd be scared of nothing.

00:17:48.120 --> 00:17:50.320
If only that donkey fell in the river.

00:17:50.720 --> 00:17:51.560
Why?

00:17:52.120 --> 00:17:53.630
Remember the Prairie Sisters?

00:17:53.670 --> 00:17:54.960
We'd pull it out.

00:17:55.480 --> 00:17:56.550
Then we'd be heroes.

00:17:57.000 --> 00:17:59.120
Then we could make up for this.

00:18:12.510 --> 00:18:13.350
Come on!

00:18:13.360 --> 00:18:14.510
Donkey, please.

00:18:14.550 --> 00:18:15.960
Laidi, help me!

00:18:15.960 --> 00:18:17.910
Come take a bath. Hurry!

00:18:17.910 --> 00:18:19.960
Donkey, only you can save us now.

00:18:20.000 --> 00:18:22.550
Just get in, bathe, then go back. Please!

00:18:22.550 --> 00:18:24.270
Laidi, help me!

00:18:29.720 --> 00:18:31.600
Go down! Go! Go!

00:18:37.270 --> 00:18:38.720
Hands up! Drop the weapon!

00:18:39.630 --> 00:18:41.510
Hands up! Drop the weapon!

00:18:43.160 --> 00:18:44.200
Hands up!

00:18:48.030 --> 00:18:49.400
My leg!

00:18:50.620 --> 00:18:55.460
(Office)

00:18:57.070 --> 00:18:58.070
A fracture in the lower leg.

00:18:58.070 --> 00:18:59.640
The soft tissue around it is injured too.

00:19:00.720 --> 00:19:01.640
Is it serious?

00:19:01.880 --> 00:19:03.200
Depends on who you're comparing her to.

00:19:03.200 --> 00:19:04.040
Over there, we still have

00:19:04.060 --> 00:19:05.440
dozens of people injured from Tangshan.

00:19:07.240 --> 00:19:10.030
Will she limp later on?

00:19:10.030 --> 00:19:12.070
Once healed, walking won't be affected.

00:19:12.480 --> 00:19:13.320
And practice routines?

00:19:13.920 --> 00:19:14.760
What?

00:19:14.880 --> 00:19:15.720
What routines?

00:19:16.510 --> 00:19:18.000
She's a troupe trainee.

00:19:18.000 --> 00:19:19.160
She has to train.

00:19:20.030 --> 00:19:21.110
That depends on her luck.

00:19:27.550 --> 00:19:28.680
You really are something.

00:19:29.590 --> 00:19:31.030
I was only away for a while,

00:19:31.350 --> 00:19:32.880
and you've caused this huge mess.

00:19:34.750 --> 00:19:35.960
Is Heiwa all right?

00:19:36.590 --> 00:19:38.200
His aunt beat him hard.

00:19:38.200 --> 00:19:39.960
He's in bed, just like you.

00:19:41.350 --> 00:19:43.350
Remember, don't say a word

00:19:43.830 --> 00:19:45.000
to anyone.

00:19:45.510 --> 00:19:47.240
Huang Zhengjing feared it'd blow up

00:19:47.240 --> 00:19:48.680
and come back on him.

00:19:48.680 --> 00:19:49.790
So he won't say anything.

00:19:52.790 --> 00:19:53.630
What's this?

00:19:53.960 --> 00:19:55.640
A letter from Aunt Hua.

00:19:56.510 --> 00:19:57.640
You little rascal.

00:19:57.640 --> 00:19:59.030
Why give it to me only now?

00:20:08.070 --> 00:20:08.910
What's this?

00:20:10.160 --> 00:20:11.030
It's been soaked through.

00:20:11.440 --> 00:20:12.790
I can't read a single word.

00:20:13.550 --> 00:20:14.550
What did she say?

00:20:15.070 --> 00:20:20.000
She said she was going
somewhere she didn't want to,

00:20:20.550 --> 00:20:21.880
for something big.

00:20:24.200 --> 00:20:25.310
She didn't say when she'd be back.

00:20:32.790 --> 00:20:34.270
Think. What else did she say?

00:20:35.110 --> 00:20:36.550
She also said...

00:20:37.750 --> 00:20:41.160
You're... a spineless coward.

00:20:44.240 --> 00:20:45.750
Don't say that to the kid.

00:20:46.240 --> 00:20:47.550
Sorry, Uncle.

00:20:48.640 --> 00:20:49.590
Not your fault.

00:20:50.590 --> 00:20:53.350
Your uncle was ruined by that jumper.

00:20:54.200 --> 00:20:55.750
She got me and Qiu

00:20:55.750 --> 00:20:57.680
held two days, mixing mud.

00:21:02.480 --> 00:21:03.750
It really is you.

00:21:04.590 --> 00:21:05.440
Why is it you?

00:21:06.720 --> 00:21:08.030
You brought in another one?

00:21:10.000 --> 00:21:11.830
My niece got kicked by a donkey.

00:21:12.160 --> 00:21:13.480
What did you mean just now?

00:21:13.920 --> 00:21:15.550
I ruined you?

00:21:16.750 --> 00:21:18.480
No matter what,

00:21:19.240 --> 00:21:21.510
you couldn't just jump from that building.

00:21:21.510 --> 00:21:23.030
It was because you yelled.

00:21:25.070 --> 00:21:26.440
A bad guy like you

00:21:26.440 --> 00:21:28.880
gets out after just two days?

00:21:28.880 --> 00:21:29.720
I'll file a complaint!

00:21:30.070 --> 00:21:31.000
Murderer.

00:21:31.480 --> 00:21:32.480
Alright, I understand you.

00:21:33.440 --> 00:21:35.880
But I've been held and lectured.

00:21:35.880 --> 00:21:37.480
And you look fine.

00:21:37.480 --> 00:21:38.880
You were only held for two days.

00:21:38.880 --> 00:21:41.750
What about my medical and recovery costs?

00:21:41.750 --> 00:21:42.590
I'll pay.

00:21:43.070 --> 00:21:43.910
I'll cover it.

00:21:44.030 --> 00:21:44.920
You said it.

00:21:52.440 --> 00:21:53.720
When she broke a leg,

00:21:53.720 --> 00:21:54.830
she could ask me to pay.

00:21:55.510 --> 00:21:56.350
But can you ask

00:21:56.510 --> 00:21:57.440
the donkey to pay?

00:21:57.960 --> 00:21:59.000
What do you mean?

00:22:19.510 --> 00:22:20.830
In those days,

00:22:21.120 --> 00:22:23.830
in the troupe, everyone

00:22:23.830 --> 00:22:25.640
ate and lived together

00:22:25.640 --> 00:22:27.920
like one big family.

00:22:28.510 --> 00:22:30.310
Day by day, life

00:22:30.920 --> 00:22:34.030
has to keep moving forward.

00:22:48.590 --> 00:22:49.640
I asked someone

00:22:50.110 --> 00:22:52.030
to buy pork bones and made the soup.

00:22:52.640 --> 00:22:53.790
Eat like to nourish like.

00:22:54.440 --> 00:22:55.510
Have some soup.

00:22:58.510 --> 00:23:00.160
Did you stew the specimens?

00:23:00.640 --> 00:23:01.750
So shattered.

00:23:02.590 --> 00:23:04.510
Meaty bones need meat coupons.

00:23:04.510 --> 00:23:05.510
I don't have any.

00:23:06.960 --> 00:23:08.750
You didn't even bring a white Mo.

00:23:08.750 --> 00:23:10.960
To recall past hardships and
appreciate today's blessings?

00:23:12.000 --> 00:23:13.920
Our work unit is short on grain.

00:23:13.920 --> 00:23:15.480
Refined grain got swapped
for coarse grain.

00:23:15.480 --> 00:23:17.110
One jin of refined grain
for two jin of coarse grain.

00:23:21.000 --> 00:23:22.590
What do you do at the Grain Bureau?

00:23:23.440 --> 00:23:24.280
Serve the cause.

00:23:25.750 --> 00:23:27.200
Then let me report something.

00:23:28.310 --> 00:23:29.640
In the troupe,

00:23:29.640 --> 00:23:31.350
we recruited dozens of trainees.

00:23:32.590 --> 00:23:34.000
Their grain ration is set

00:23:34.000 --> 00:23:35.160
by the student standard.

00:23:35.160 --> 00:23:36.880
Twenty-one jin per person each month.

00:23:36.880 --> 00:23:37.790
That's nowhere near enough.

00:23:38.270 --> 00:23:39.790
The kids practice routines daily.

00:23:39.790 --> 00:23:41.270
They burn through tons of energy.

00:23:42.160 --> 00:23:43.440
They're all starving like wolves.

00:23:43.880 --> 00:23:44.960
My niece alone

00:23:44.960 --> 00:23:46.440
starts with four Mo a meal.

00:23:47.830 --> 00:23:49.680
That grain ration isn't nearly enough.

00:23:50.310 --> 00:23:51.680
Can you pull a few strings?

00:23:52.160 --> 00:23:53.680
Raise the grain ration a bit?

00:23:54.070 --> 00:23:55.070
You sure ask a lot.

00:23:55.070 --> 00:23:57.240
Use the front door. I have no back door.

00:23:57.750 --> 00:23:58.720
Get this done for me,

00:23:59.880 --> 00:24:01.550
and I'll get you a pork knuckle later.

00:24:03.720 --> 00:24:04.560
Like this?

00:24:05.550 --> 00:24:07.350
Next time, I'll stew meaty bones for you.

00:24:07.350 --> 00:24:08.350
I'll borrow some meat coupons.

00:24:08.750 --> 00:24:09.960
Liar.

00:24:10.790 --> 00:24:11.750
You get this handled for me,

00:24:11.750 --> 00:24:13.310
and I'll pull strings for you too.

00:24:14.000 --> 00:24:16.480
You'll watch shows for free for life.

00:24:20.680 --> 00:24:21.920
I'm not with the Grain Bureau.

00:24:22.920 --> 00:24:24.160
You are not?

00:24:24.160 --> 00:24:25.920
You jumped from their building.

00:24:26.310 --> 00:24:27.240
Because someone

00:24:27.240 --> 00:24:29.160
set me up with a Grain Bureau date.

00:24:29.550 --> 00:24:31.440
That day, I'd just gone upstairs.

00:24:31.440 --> 00:24:32.480
I hadn't even met the man.

00:24:32.480 --> 00:24:34.480
Then you yelled, "Earthquake!"

00:24:35.350 --> 00:24:36.190
And then?

00:24:36.440 --> 00:24:37.680
Then I ended up lying here.

00:24:39.640 --> 00:24:41.510
So you two never met, right?

00:24:41.510 --> 00:24:42.510
How?

00:24:42.510 --> 00:24:43.640
How could we meet?

00:24:44.640 --> 00:24:45.480
Right, right.

00:24:46.350 --> 00:24:47.680
Come on, drink the soup.

00:24:50.310 --> 00:24:51.440
Finish the soft cartilage.

00:24:53.000 --> 00:24:54.350
I'll crack the bone later.

00:24:54.920 --> 00:24:55.760
There's bone marrow.

00:24:57.830 --> 00:24:58.670
Easy, easy.

00:25:00.350 --> 00:25:02.070
Don't break it. We'll need it later.

00:25:02.680 --> 00:25:03.920
Come on, give me a hand.

00:25:03.920 --> 00:25:06.310
We just said the troupe was family.

00:25:06.720 --> 00:25:07.750
Now we're tearing it down.

00:25:08.310 --> 00:25:09.550
It's hard to let go.

00:25:10.000 --> 00:25:11.310
These past few months felt like

00:25:11.750 --> 00:25:12.960
being on a swing.

00:25:13.240 --> 00:25:14.080
Back and forth.

00:25:16.110 --> 00:25:17.510
Like a play.

00:25:17.920 --> 00:25:19.680
A play? What kind of play?

00:25:20.440 --> 00:25:21.510
One without a script,

00:25:22.720 --> 00:25:24.200
where you can't guess the ending.

00:25:30.030 --> 00:25:31.790
The weather's nice today.

00:25:31.790 --> 00:25:33.110
And it's a day to celebrate.

00:25:33.590 --> 00:25:35.310
I'm taking you out for some air.

00:25:36.110 --> 00:25:37.510
What are we celebrating?

00:25:38.000 --> 00:25:39.640
A day for nationwide celebration.

00:25:45.510 --> 00:25:46.350
Look over there.

00:25:46.640 --> 00:25:47.960
Wave, wave.

00:25:48.400 --> 00:25:52.170
笙ｪThe fine wine smells so sweet笙ｪ

00:25:52.200 --> 00:25:54.000
It's so lively.

00:25:57.240 --> 00:26:00.480
笙ｪMy friend, please raise a glass笙ｪ

00:26:02.440 --> 00:26:04.270
The troupe is here! They're here!

00:26:05.160 --> 00:26:06.480
The troupe is here!

00:26:08.310 --> 00:26:10.440
The troupe is here! They're here!

00:26:16.110 --> 00:26:17.640
Thank you, comrades!

00:26:18.480 --> 00:26:19.680
Have some water.

00:26:19.680 --> 00:26:21.440
I'm here to refill everyone's water.

00:26:21.440 --> 00:26:22.310
Here, here.

00:26:23.240 --> 00:26:24.830
Come on, come on.

00:26:24.830 --> 00:26:26.000
There's sugar in it.

00:26:28.720 --> 00:26:29.560
Sweet, huh?

00:26:29.830 --> 00:26:30.720
I added sugar.

00:26:30.720 --> 00:26:31.580
It's sweet!

00:26:31.580 --> 00:26:33.200
- I added sugar.
- How's your leg?

00:26:33.510 --> 00:26:34.350
Much better.

00:26:35.750 --> 00:26:37.830
What are you doing? Fall in!

00:26:39.830 --> 00:26:40.750
Hurry, hurry.

00:26:40.750 --> 00:26:41.950
Drink up and get going.

00:26:41.950 --> 00:26:42.790
Sweet.

00:26:42.790 --> 00:26:43.720
Or Huang Zhengjing

00:26:43.720 --> 00:26:44.680
will ramble again.

00:26:45.140 --> 00:26:46.030
Okay.

00:26:46.030 --> 00:26:47.440
Okay, okay. Fill it up.

00:26:47.440 --> 00:26:48.300
Hey.

00:26:48.310 --> 00:26:49.640
Why bring two injured folks?

00:26:50.070 --> 00:26:51.270
Laidi's hospital buddy.

00:26:51.720 --> 00:26:53.440
I brought them out for fresh air.

00:26:54.110 --> 00:26:54.960
Keep dancing.

00:26:54.960 --> 00:26:56.640
Huang Zhengjing's rambling again.

00:26:57.640 --> 00:27:01.120
笙ｪA bright future is guided ahead笙ｪ

00:27:01.120 --> 00:27:05.230
笙ｪVast rivers and hills glow at dawn笙ｪ

00:27:05.240 --> 00:27:07.350
See that young guy? That one.

00:27:07.830 --> 00:27:08.670
Which one?

00:27:09.070 --> 00:27:10.750
The one dancing badly.

00:27:11.110 --> 00:27:11.950
He

00:27:12.160 --> 00:27:14.880
handles stage design for our troupe.

00:27:14.880 --> 00:27:15.750
What's stage design?

00:27:16.110 --> 00:27:17.960
He takes care of the sets onstage.

00:27:19.720 --> 00:27:22.440
He's key staff in the troupe, got it?

00:27:22.920 --> 00:27:25.440
His family are poor
and lower-middle peasants.

00:27:25.440 --> 00:27:26.440
A perfect background!

00:27:27.030 --> 00:27:29.030
He has skills too. He does carpentry.

00:27:29.920 --> 00:27:32.270
The big wardrobe at home,

00:27:32.270 --> 00:27:34.790
the bookcase, the nightstands, all his.

00:27:35.830 --> 00:27:37.920
All he needs now is a girlfriend.

00:27:38.310 --> 00:27:40.160
How about I play matchmaker?

00:27:40.550 --> 00:27:41.830
I'll introduce you two.

00:27:42.720 --> 00:27:44.640
Nail, dance your best.

00:27:47.360 --> 00:27:51.560
笙ｪCome, come, come笙ｪ

00:27:51.560 --> 00:27:53.800
笙ｪOn the road, the drums beat笙ｪ

00:27:53.800 --> 00:27:56.160
笙ｪGood news flies from every front笙ｪ

00:27:56.160 --> 00:28:00.540
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

00:28:47.110 --> 00:28:48.590
When will Aunt Hua be back?

00:28:54.160 --> 00:28:55.200
Missing her?

00:28:55.640 --> 00:28:56.830
Will she come back?

00:28:58.070 --> 00:28:58.910
She will.

00:29:00.960 --> 00:29:02.310
Her stage is here.

00:29:02.310 --> 00:29:03.640
Where else would she go?

00:29:07.920 --> 00:29:09.790
Careful. Don't fall.

00:29:24.070 --> 00:29:26.550
Like the princess dress I made for you?

00:29:29.070 --> 00:29:30.030
Turn around. Let me see.

00:29:36.960 --> 00:29:38.550
You're the Ugly Duckling.

00:29:39.160 --> 00:29:40.160
No, I'm not.

00:29:41.640 --> 00:29:42.480
Silly.

00:29:42.920 --> 00:29:44.000
It looks plain

00:29:44.550 --> 00:29:46.030
because it hasn't grown up yet.

00:29:47.070 --> 00:29:48.440
Once it grows up,

00:29:49.240 --> 00:29:50.920
it becomes a white swan.

00:29:51.640 --> 00:29:53.680
Then it can fly anywhere it wants.

00:30:01.200 --> 00:30:02.270
Did you thank Aunt Bai?

00:30:03.270 --> 00:30:05.750
Not Aunt. Call me Shoes Bai.

00:30:06.790 --> 00:30:08.830
We're best friends, right?

00:30:13.000 --> 00:30:13.880
Hu Sanyuan.

00:30:15.480 --> 00:30:16.750
I need to ask you a favor.

00:30:17.160 --> 00:30:18.270
Don't be so polite.

00:30:18.680 --> 00:30:19.590
Just tell me.

00:30:20.720 --> 00:30:21.790
Today's his birthday.

00:30:22.160 --> 00:30:23.110
Could you take me

00:30:23.110 --> 00:30:24.350
to celebrate it with him?

00:30:26.480 --> 00:30:28.200
Sure. Where?

00:30:29.440 --> 00:30:30.830
Somewhere close to him.

00:31:53.070 --> 00:31:55.200
That day on the barren hillside,

00:31:55.590 --> 00:32:00.270
Yi Qing'e learned a pain called afterpain.

00:32:00.750 --> 00:32:03.240
A pain that could last a lifetime.

00:32:50.480 --> 00:32:51.640
Why is she crying?

00:32:52.830 --> 00:32:53.680
Let her cry.

00:32:55.070 --> 00:32:56.640
It's better for tears

00:32:57.160 --> 00:32:58.750
to come out than to stay in the heart.

00:33:05.920 --> 00:33:07.640
Left, right, left!

00:33:07.640 --> 00:33:10.440
One, two, three, four!

00:33:10.440 --> 00:33:13.200
Be determined!

00:33:13.200 --> 00:33:16.070
Be determined!

00:33:16.070 --> 00:33:18.880
Fear no sacrifice!

00:33:18.880 --> 00:33:19.790
Fear no sacrifice!

00:33:19.790 --> 00:33:20.630
Say it with them!

00:33:20.920 --> 00:33:22.030
Get your voice going too!

00:33:22.310 --> 00:33:24.160
Overcome every obstacle!

00:33:24.160 --> 00:33:25.590
Fight for victory!

00:33:25.590 --> 00:33:27.350
Fight for victory!

00:33:27.350 --> 00:33:29.920
One, two, three, four!

00:33:30.270 --> 00:33:31.880
One, two, three, four.

00:33:31.880 --> 00:33:33.310
Be determined!

00:33:33.310 --> 00:33:35.240
Be determined!

00:33:35.240 --> 00:33:36.960
Fear no sacrifice!

00:33:36.960 --> 00:33:38.720
Fear no sacrifice!

00:33:38.720 --> 00:33:40.480
Overcome every obstacle!

00:33:40.480 --> 00:33:42.270
Overcome every obstacle!

00:33:42.270 --> 00:33:43.880
Fight for victory!

00:33:43.880 --> 00:33:45.510
Fight for victory!

00:34:37.110 --> 00:34:39.030
Why knock? I'm awake.

00:34:39.030 --> 00:34:40.590
Didn't you hear your niece

00:34:40.590 --> 00:34:41.720
singing?

00:34:43.310 --> 00:34:45.110
I heard her. She sounded fine.

00:34:46.510 --> 00:34:47.880
You call that fine?

00:34:48.590 --> 00:34:50.960
She dragged down the whole class.

00:34:50.960 --> 00:34:51.800
Can't you tell?

00:34:52.310 --> 00:34:53.270
What's the big deal?

00:34:54.000 --> 00:34:56.070
Even Hua Caixiang got dragged down.

00:34:56.070 --> 00:34:57.110
Who else could manage that?

00:34:58.110 --> 00:34:59.030
Fine, fine.

00:34:59.030 --> 00:35:00.030
Listen,

00:35:00.030 --> 00:35:01.510
right now, in a crowd,

00:35:02.310 --> 00:35:03.550
she can still blend in.

00:35:03.960 --> 00:35:05.110
But once

00:35:05.110 --> 00:35:06.070
the exam starts,

00:35:06.070 --> 00:35:07.680
they'll assign training tracks.

00:35:08.200 --> 00:35:10.510
Then, whatever she's got,

00:35:10.510 --> 00:35:11.590
she'll have to show it.

00:35:12.920 --> 00:35:14.480
She's this stiff,

00:35:14.880 --> 00:35:16.720
this uncoordinated, and she

00:35:16.720 --> 00:35:18.000
sings like that.

00:35:18.350 --> 00:35:20.160
At best, she belongs

00:35:20.160 --> 00:35:21.590
on the scarecrow track.

00:35:22.550 --> 00:35:24.750
Just days of basic skills, and role type?

00:35:25.480 --> 00:35:26.830
In other counties,

00:35:26.830 --> 00:35:28.720
young trainees are already onstage.

00:35:28.720 --> 00:35:30.550
It's driving Huang Zhengjing mad.

00:35:30.880 --> 00:35:32.110
He needs results, fast.

00:35:32.640 --> 00:35:33.720
Find a way, now.

00:35:34.270 --> 00:35:35.790
Don't say I didn't warn you then.

00:35:36.590 --> 00:35:37.430
Still sleeping?

00:35:37.920 --> 00:35:38.790
That's ridiculous!

00:35:40.070 --> 00:35:40.910
Mi Lan.

00:35:41.240 --> 00:35:43.160
Until her leg gets better,

00:35:43.160 --> 00:35:44.070
just take my tricycle

00:35:44.070 --> 00:35:45.960
whenever you go to morning practice.

00:35:46.480 --> 00:35:47.670
I wouldn't dare.

00:35:47.670 --> 00:35:49.960
Or someone would eat me alive.

00:35:50.280 --> 00:35:52.190
Who would dare?

00:35:52.190 --> 00:35:53.280
I wouldn't allow it.

00:35:54.590 --> 00:35:55.590
I got your word.

00:35:56.510 --> 00:35:57.670
Pretty tough-sounding.

00:35:58.150 --> 00:36:00.320
So, what favor are you suddenly

00:36:00.320 --> 00:36:01.590
asking for?

00:36:02.590 --> 00:36:03.880
How's her singing?

00:36:04.320 --> 00:36:05.480
Don't you have ears?

00:36:06.320 --> 00:36:08.480
Her pitch is off. Can that be fixed?

00:36:08.880 --> 00:36:10.510
Hard to say.

00:36:10.510 --> 00:36:13.150
Some kids sing off-key
because their technique is wrong.

00:36:13.150 --> 00:36:15.590
With training, they can be corrected.

00:36:16.320 --> 00:36:18.670
But if they simply don't have the talent,

00:36:18.670 --> 00:36:19.760
then there's nothing you can do.

00:36:20.280 --> 00:36:21.440
He Dachui said

00:36:21.710 --> 00:36:23.000
there's an exam coming up.

00:36:23.760 --> 00:36:25.760
Give the kid some intensive coaching

00:36:26.150 --> 00:36:27.000
and help her fix it.

00:36:29.150 --> 00:36:29.990
Sanyuan,

00:36:30.440 --> 00:36:31.590
there's something

00:36:31.590 --> 00:36:33.230
you may not like hearing.

00:36:34.960 --> 00:36:37.480
But if she truly doesn't have the talent,

00:36:37.480 --> 00:36:40.630
you shouldn't push her.
That wouldn't be fair to her.

00:36:40.630 --> 00:36:41.840
I really don't like hearing that.

00:36:41.840 --> 00:36:43.360
How can you say she has no talent?

00:36:43.920 --> 00:36:48.670
笙ｪTwo tigers. Two tigers笙ｪ

00:36:48.670 --> 00:36:53.230
笙ｪRun fast. Run fast笙ｪ

00:36:53.230 --> 00:36:54.880
Ready, sing.

00:36:55.000 --> 00:36:57.320
笙ｪTwo tigers. Two tigers笙ｪ

00:36:57.320 --> 00:36:59.280
笙ｪRun fast. Run fast笙ｪ

00:37:00.510 --> 00:37:02.000
You... Step back a little.

00:37:03.320 --> 00:37:04.190
I'm sitting this close,

00:37:04.190 --> 00:37:05.480
and I do have ears.

00:37:05.480 --> 00:37:06.510
I can hear you.

00:37:06.510 --> 00:37:08.360
Could you lower your voice?

00:37:08.360 --> 00:37:09.480
Also,

00:37:09.480 --> 00:37:11.230
follow the teacher's rhythm.

00:37:11.670 --> 00:37:12.920
Follow the piano.

00:37:12.920 --> 00:37:14.070
Don't rush the beat.

00:37:14.070 --> 00:37:15.440
Ready, and go.

00:37:18.190 --> 00:37:19.880
What's with her today?

00:37:19.880 --> 00:37:21.960
No idea. She's usually fine.

00:37:21.960 --> 00:37:24.320
Shoes Bai, what are you doing?

00:37:24.840 --> 00:37:26.710
Yeah, why dance here today?

00:37:27.130 --> 00:37:28.000
The show's on.

00:37:28.000 --> 00:37:29.630
Quiet, quiet.

00:37:29.670 --> 00:37:30.510
Quiet.

00:37:30.670 --> 00:37:33.150
The snowflakes...

00:37:33.150 --> 00:37:35.320
Shoes Bai, come down.

00:37:35.320 --> 00:37:36.480
Careful, you might fall.

00:37:36.480 --> 00:37:37.440
Come down. Come down.

00:37:37.440 --> 00:37:38.880
Listen. Come down, now.

00:37:38.880 --> 00:37:40.000
Careful, you might fall.

00:37:40.000 --> 00:37:41.320
- Quiet.
- You might fall.

00:37:41.320 --> 00:37:42.160
The show's on. Go.

00:37:42.510 --> 00:37:44.090
Listen. Come down before you fall.

00:37:44.100 --> 00:37:45.030
You'll fall.

00:37:45.030 --> 00:37:46.630
Hurry down. Down, down.

00:37:46.630 --> 00:37:47.840
Come down, now.

00:37:47.840 --> 00:37:49.150
What's going on?

00:37:49.800 --> 00:37:51.030
- No idea.
- What's going on?

00:37:51.030 --> 00:37:51.870
She seems crazy.

00:37:52.070 --> 00:37:53.190
Stay away from me!

00:37:53.190 --> 00:37:54.280
- Shoes Bai!
- Shoes Bai!

00:37:54.280 --> 00:37:55.130
Shoes Bai!

00:37:55.130 --> 00:37:56.590
Shoes Bai has lost it!

00:37:57.190 --> 00:37:58.360
Shoes Bai has lost it!

00:37:58.360 --> 00:37:59.320
Shoes Bai has lost it!

00:38:00.630 --> 00:38:01.480
Shoes Bai!

00:38:02.570 --> 00:38:03.510
Shoes Bai!

00:38:03.510 --> 00:38:04.360
Stop her!

00:38:09.880 --> 00:38:10.720
Uncle!

00:38:11.230 --> 00:38:12.070
Uncle!

00:38:12.280 --> 00:38:13.960
What's the rush? Slow down.

00:38:13.960 --> 00:38:14.880
Don't fall.

00:38:14.880 --> 00:38:16.070
Something's off with Shoes Bai.

00:38:16.920 --> 00:38:17.840
Off how?

00:38:18.230 --> 00:38:19.360
I don't know.

00:38:19.360 --> 00:38:20.630
Go check on her.

00:38:23.550 --> 00:38:25.110
She's gone mad! Stay back!

00:38:28.630 --> 00:38:29.760
What are you doing?

00:38:31.510 --> 00:38:32.360
What are you doing?

00:38:32.360 --> 00:38:33.210
Go.

00:38:33.230 --> 00:38:34.670
Back off! What are you doing?

00:38:35.510 --> 00:38:36.350
Hu Sanyuan.

00:38:37.150 --> 00:38:37.990
Have you lost it?

00:38:38.440 --> 00:38:39.760
Who gave you the right to tie her up?

00:38:40.630 --> 00:38:42.320
She's gone mad. She needs a hospital.

00:38:42.320 --> 00:38:43.760
- Still can't tie her up.
- Are you crazy?

00:38:43.760 --> 00:38:44.800
Who gave you the right to tie her up?

00:38:45.230 --> 00:38:46.190
Try tying me up.

00:38:46.590 --> 00:38:47.840
She's gone mad. She needs a hospital.

00:38:47.840 --> 00:38:48.680
Are you crazy?

00:38:49.480 --> 00:38:52.360
Hu Sanyuan, you'll answer for this.

00:38:53.590 --> 00:38:55.000
You rotten jerk.

00:38:57.670 --> 00:38:58.710
It's okay now.

00:38:59.550 --> 00:39:00.390
It's okay.

00:39:02.190 --> 00:39:03.550
Her only family is her old mother.

00:39:03.960 --> 00:39:04.800
And she can't come.

00:39:05.320 --> 00:39:07.550
Director Huang wants the
Security Section to send her.

00:39:08.760 --> 00:39:10.070
That Security Section bunch...

00:39:12.480 --> 00:39:13.440
Let me send her.

00:39:14.000 --> 00:39:16.070
Have a female comrade
from the troupe with me.

00:39:16.510 --> 00:39:17.880
It's not right for you to send her.

00:39:18.150 --> 00:39:19.230
How is it not right?

00:39:19.230 --> 00:39:20.550
You know how.

00:39:20.920 --> 00:39:22.150
Then I'll send her.

00:39:22.920 --> 00:39:24.710
Hu Sanyuan can help me.

00:39:26.150 --> 00:39:26.990
Will that work?

00:39:28.920 --> 00:39:29.960
I'll ask Director Huang.

00:39:30.920 --> 00:39:32.360
Is he your dad?

00:39:32.360 --> 00:39:33.280
No, my grandpa.

00:39:53.940 --> 00:40:00.940
(Hundreds of flowers bloom)

00:40:03.590 --> 00:40:04.430
Did she eat?

00:40:05.030 --> 00:40:07.150
Some porridge and half a Mo.

00:40:09.000 --> 00:40:09.840
That's good.

00:40:13.070 --> 00:40:14.280
All right. Sleep early.

00:40:14.670 --> 00:40:15.630
Don't just sit here.

00:40:18.920 --> 00:40:21.320
Tomorrow, Mi Lan and I will take her back

00:40:22.880 --> 00:40:24.670
to her mom. Maybe she'll

00:40:24.920 --> 00:40:26.000
get better.

00:40:27.510 --> 00:40:28.800
Will she come back?

00:40:30.150 --> 00:40:31.150
No, she won't.

00:40:32.960 --> 00:40:34.190
She never belonged here.

00:42:03.190 --> 00:42:05.440
Shoes Bai is gone.

00:42:05.440 --> 00:42:06.630
She flew away.

00:42:07.400 --> 00:42:09.840
No one knows where she went.

00:42:10.710 --> 00:42:12.150
She is a swan.

00:42:12.760 --> 00:42:14.880
She was never meant to be trapped here.

00:42:15.480 --> 00:42:17.440
But where is her sky?

00:42:17.630 --> 00:42:18.480
And where

00:42:18.480 --> 00:42:20.670
is her Swan Lake?

00:42:22.510 --> 00:42:23.630
Many years later,

00:42:23.630 --> 00:42:26.960
when Yi Qing'e felt most lost,

00:42:26.960 --> 00:42:30.030
that swan kept appearing to her,

00:42:30.510 --> 00:42:32.360
as if trying to tell her something.

00:42:33.190 --> 00:42:35.590
To hold on to that purity within

00:42:35.590 --> 00:42:37.030
and never compromise.

00:42:37.670 --> 00:42:41.030
To look up, spread her wings, and fly.

00:42:42.230 --> 00:42:44.320
Yi Qing'e kept asking herself

00:42:45.480 --> 00:42:47.920
where her own sky was,

00:42:48.230 --> 00:42:49.070
and where

00:42:49.670 --> 00:42:52.070
her own Swan Lake was.

00:43:05.020 --> 00:43:06.940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

00:43:09.110 --> 00:43:10.000
I've decided

00:43:10.000 --> 00:43:10.960
to go to Zhang Guangrong's.

00:43:11.030 --> 00:43:13.400
This is your home turf, your base,

00:43:13.400 --> 00:43:14.280
your stronghold.

00:43:14.320 --> 00:43:16.400
We must get ahead of everyone,

00:43:16.400 --> 00:43:17.510
and stage this play first.

00:43:17.510 --> 00:43:18.920
Everyone in the troupe

00:43:18.920 --> 00:43:20.670
is like monkeys loose from Mount Huaguo.

00:43:20.880 --> 00:43:23.320
Now I'm Peng Batian.

00:43:23.360 --> 00:43:24.400
Use a homemade cannon

00:43:24.400 --> 00:43:26.150
to blast down Peng Batian's yard wall.

00:43:28.550 --> 00:43:29.550
Will it work?

00:43:29.550 --> 00:43:30.390
Light it.

00:43:37.000 --> 00:43:41.620
笙ｪWhen I woke up and turned back笙ｪ

00:43:43.090 --> 00:43:47.930
笙ｪI wasn't sure where to go笙ｪ

00:43:49.370 --> 00:43:53.560
笙ｪWe met and brushed past笙ｪ

00:43:55.120 --> 00:44:02.420
笙ｪYour shadow drifted out of sight笙ｪ

00:44:16.790 --> 00:44:20.540
笙ｪThe stove fire blazed in my dream笙ｪ

00:44:22.140 --> 00:44:27.710
笙ｪLit up the tracks of pearly tears笙ｪ

00:44:28.830 --> 00:44:32.890
笙ｪIn my dream, water sleeves flew笙ｪ

00:44:34.020 --> 00:44:39.610
笙ｪHiding a lifetime of love笙ｪ

00:44:40.770 --> 00:44:44.970
笙ｪThe Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage笙ｪ

00:44:46.010 --> 00:44:51.640
笙ｪSpring water brewed strong wine笙ｪ

00:44:52.810 --> 00:44:57.500
笙ｪSheep moved through the valley笙ｪ

00:44:58.180 --> 00:45:03.350
笙ｪIt felt like a promise
from another life笙ｪ

00:45:04.020 --> 00:45:09.050
笙ｪWhen I woke up and turned back笙ｪ

00:45:10.080 --> 00:45:15.510
笙ｪI wasn't sure where to go笙ｪ

00:45:15.890 --> 00:45:21.170
笙ｪIf I chose again, I'd still roam笙ｪ

00:45:22.120 --> 00:45:27.930
笙ｪAll over this sunlit plateau笙ｪ

00:45:27.930 --> 00:45:33.350
笙ｪThe dream ends; the curtain falls笙ｪ

00:45:33.900 --> 00:45:39.410
笙ｪMoonlight washes off this stage makeup笙ｪ

00:45:39.960 --> 00:45:44.920
笙ｪThe one in the mirror wears gray hair笙ｪ

00:45:45.940 --> 00:45:51.220
笙ｪAlready sang all my joy and sorrow笙ｪ

00:45:52.020 --> 00:46:01.050
笙ｪAlready shouted across Qinchuan Plain笙ｪ